Free Collaborators
Paid users can invite an unlimited number of free collaborators. Free collaborators can edit sheets and reports, attach documents, set alerts, and participate in discussions. However, they cannot create or own sheets the way a paid user can.





See Plan Features




Support
Email + Phone
Email + Phone
Email + Phone
Email




Basic plans have access to online support tools such as the Community as well as email technical support.  Team, Business, and Enterprise plans also have access to phone technical support and will be given priority.
Online support documentation is also offered in Portuguese, Spanish, German, French, Russian, Japanese and Italian.




Free Collaborator
Unlimited
Unlimited
Unlimited
Unlimited



Free Collaborators can be anyone who is asked to participate on a project, including clients, partners, and vendors. They can view or edit sheets shared to them by Licensed Users. If people need the capability to create sheets and reports, they need to be a Licensed User.



Sheets 
Unlimited
100/User
50/User
10




Sheets store the information and files you collaborate on, track, and manage. You can set up sheets for managing projects, processes, contacts, checklists - literally anything.
                                
The number of sheets per plan is shown here. Sheet capacity is pooled and based on the number of sheets per user. Example: A 5-user Team plan provides 250 sheets (5 x 50 sheets). Sheets shared to a user by others do not count against this total.




Reports
Unlimited
Unlimited
Unlimited
View/Edit Only




Reporting allows you to pull together information across multiple sheets and filter it for a specific purpose. Reports are editable, and any edits are automatically applied to the underlying sheets. 
Create a report rolling up assigned tasks to a particular individual across different projects/sheets, or pull together a summary of multiple projects into a status report.




Mobile







Access Smartsheet from any browser on any smartphone or tablet, or download the app for iPhone, iPad or Android.




Collaboration

Attachments








You can attach almost any type of file to a workspace, sheet, row, or discussion. The vast majority of file types are supported, including image, PDF, Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint files.




Reminders








Reminders are automatic emails that are set to remind you, or your team members of upcoming task deadlines, event dates or task commencement.




Notification Rules
100/sheet
25/sheet
5/sheet
1/sheet




Notifications are automatic emails that are sent when changes are made to a sheet. Notification rules give you the ability to specify the conditions under which an email is triggered to alert recipient(s).




Comments








Comments give you the ability to have and save conversations with others about the work that you’re doing.




Activity Log


 
 




Activity Log is a single place to view and filter on all of the activities and changes made to a sheet. You can see who viewed your sheet, whom it was shared with, what changes were made, and when.  Filter by user, date range, and action types to find exactly what you’re looking for.
                                





Views

Card View








Display tasks on cards, categorize cards into lanes to organize your work more visually, drag and drop cards into different lanes to move work through a process.




Gantt Charts/Critical path








Show task and cross-project dependencies, hierarchy, milestones, percentage complete, custom fields, critical path and filters.




Calendar View








The Calendar View will display all the dates contained in a sheet or report in a calendar format. You can also sync your sheet to your Google Calendar.





User Administration

User Mgmt, Groups



 




Assign System Administrators who can add and remove users and manage sheet ownership. Assign Group Admins who can create groups for sharing/sending to multiple users.




Resource Management



 




View allocation of key people across projects.




Single Sign on (SSO)

 
 
 




Enable the use of corporate logon credentials using SAML based Single Sign-On (SSO) service. SAML2 supports ADFS 2, Okta, OneLogin, Ping Identity, VMWare Horizon, Shibboleth.




Enterprise Access Control

 
 
 




Enterprise Controls allow you to control what domains users can share to, control sheet publication features, define what types of files users can attach, define custom welcome screens for your users, and automatically add Licensed Users within designated email domains to your plan. 





Solution Building

Sights


View Only
View Only




Sights can help you visualize, summarize, and share important aspects of your work such as project status or whether you're on target with key performance indicators (KPIs). A Sight can also help you stay organized by providing a hub, or central location, for related resources such as collections of sheets or reports.
                                




Forms








Configure and publish web based forms for collecting data into a sheet. Common uses include collecting survey data, customer feedback, and applicant information.




Custom Color and Logos



 




Customize the color and logo of your Smartsheet account, web forms, and workspaces.





Integrations

G Suite 








Smartsheet enables Gmail and G Suite users to request updates via Gmail, import contacts from Gmail, merge data with Docs, collaborate over Hangouts, attach and retrieve files from Drive, import and export to Sheets, sync with Calendar, and utilize Enterprise SSO via OAuth.




O 365 








Smartsheet enables Office 365 users to create or edit Smartsheet tasks from within both Outlook and Outlook Mobile, attach files from OneDrive, import/export to Excel and Project, collaborate with Skype for Business (requires Smartsheet Enterprise or Business plan), gain insights from Power BI, automate workflows with Flow, and sign on to Smartsheet with Azure Active Directory.
















If you have uploaded files to your Google Drive, OneDrive, Dropbox, Box, Evernote or Egnyte account you can attach a direct link to those files to a Smartsheet workspace, sheet, row, or discussion.




API Calls








The Smartsheet API enables customers to programmatically access and manage their organization's Smartsheet account and data. It is designed to be simple and intuitive, and is based on widely accepted standards and conventions, including REST, JSON, and HTTP success and error codes. If you already have experience with other publicly available RESTful APIs, you will feel right at home.




Live Data Connector


 
 




Connect live Smartsheet data to analytics tools like Tableau, Excel, Qlik, and Spotfire using an industry-standard ODBC connector.




Salesforce
Optional
Contact Us
Contact Us
 




Smartsheet for Salesforce enables powerful collaboration capabilities for sales teams to organize, update, and share customer information with internal and external team members. Data is automatically synchronized whether edited in Smartsheet or Salesforce, ensuring all stakeholders are viewing the most up-to-date information.




JIRA 
Optional
Contact Us
Contact Us
 




Smartsheet for JIRA provides visibility into IT and software development projects being tracked in JIRA. Issues are automatically synchronized whether edited in Smartsheet or JIRA, ensuring every record is up to date.





See Fewer Features






